agentSwitchMbufRisingThreshold.name: agentSwitchMbufRisingThreshold
agentSwitchMbufRisingThreshold.description: The Mbuf utilization rising threshold in percentage. A single notification (rising event) is generated when the total Mbuf utilization exceeds this threshold. After a rising event is generated, another such event will not be generated until the total Mbuf utilization falls below the agentSwitchMbufFallingThreshold and then exceeds the agentSwitchMbufRisingThreshold.

agentSwitchMbufFallingThreshold.name: agentSwitchMbufFallingThreshold
agentSwitchMbufFallingThreshold.description: The Mbuf utilization falling threshold in percentage. A single notification (falling event) is generated when the total Mbuf utilization falls below this threshold. After a falling event is generated, another such event will not be generated until the total Mbuf utilization exceeds the agentSwitchMbufRisingThreshold and then falls below the agentSwitchMbufFallingThreshold.

agentSwitchMbufNotificationSeverity.name: agentSwitchMbufNotificationSeverity
agentSwitchMbufNotificationSeverity.description: Severity level while notification is generated for rising and falling threshold.

agentDigitalSignatureVerifyMode.name: agentDigitalSignatureVerifyMode
agentDigitalSignatureVerifyMode.description: To configure the digital signature verify option for the downloading image and config files. The selected option is stored in config data. The following options are supported: noverify - no digital signature verification of image or config script file image - digital signature verification of image only config - digital signature verification of config script only all - digital signature verification of image and config script file

agentSaveConfig.name: agentSaveConfig
agentSaveConfig.description: enable(1) will initiate an configuration save to nvram. Status is returned by the object agentSaveConfigStatus.

agentResetSystem.name: agentResetSystem
agentResetSystem.description: Resets the switch. This object is not valid for stacking platforms.

agentSaveConfigStatus.name: agentSaveConfigStatus
agentSaveConfigStatus.description: Indicates the current status of an save configuration request.

agentStartupConfigErase.name: agentStartupConfigErase
agentStartupConfigErase.description: Erase the text-based configuration named startup-config stored in non-volatile memory.On read returns 0.

agentFactoryDefaultsErase.name: agentFactoryDefaultsErase
agentFactoryDefaultsErase.description: Erase the text-based configuration file named factory-defaults stored in non-volatile memory.On read returns 0.

agentCableTesterStatus.name: agentCableTesterStatus
agentCableTesterStatus.description: Status of the Virtual Cable Tester active(1) - cable testing is in progress. Set to this value to start the test. success(2) - A successful test was performed. Cannot be set. failure(3) - A failure was encountered during the test. Cannot be set. uninitialized(4) - No test has been performed yet. Cannot be set.

agentCableTesterIfIndex.name: agentCableTesterIfIndex
agentCableTesterIfIndex.description: Determines on which port to perform the cable test. Limited to copper based ports.

agentCableTesterCableStatus.name: agentCableTesterCableStatus
agentCableTesterCableStatus.description: Indicates the results of the Cable Test. normal(1) - The cable is working correctly. open(2) - The cable is disconnected or there is a faulty connector. short(3) - There is an electrical short in the cable. unknown(4) - No test has been performed yet, or a test is currently in progress.

agentCableTesterMinimumCableLength.name: agentCableTesterMinimumCableLength
agentCableTesterMinimumCableLength.description: The estimated length of the cable in meters. This value indicates the shortest length estimated. This object will return 0 if agentCableTesterStatus is not success(2) or the cable length is unknown.

agentCableTesterMaximumCableLength.name: agentCableTesterMaximumCableLength
agentCableTesterMaximumCableLength.description: The estimated length of the cable in meters. This value indicates the longest length estimated. This object will return 0 if agentCableTesterStatus is not success(2) or the cable length is unknown.

agentCableTesterCableFailureLocation.name: agentCableTesterCableFailureLocation
agentCableTesterCableFailureLocation.description: The estimated distance in meters from the end of the cable to the failure location. This object will return 0 if agentCableTesterStatus is not success(2).

agentDaiSrcMacValidate.name: agentDaiSrcMacValidate
agentDaiSrcMacValidate.description: This object indicates whether Sender MAC validation in the ARP packets is enabled. If this object is set to 'true', validation is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', validation is disabled.

agentDaiDstMacValidate.name: agentDaiDstMacValidate
agentDaiDstMacValidate.description: This object indicates whether Target MAC validation in the ARP Response packets is enabled. If this object is set to 'true', validation is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', validation is disabled.

agentDaiIPValidate.name: agentDaiIPValidate
agentDaiIPValidate.description: This object indicates whether IP address validation in the ARP packets is enabled. If this object is set to 'true', validation is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', validation is disabled.

agentDaiVlanConfigTable.name: agentDaiVlanConfigTable
agentDaiVlanConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to control Dynamic ARP Inspection per VLAN. When a VLAN is created in a device supporting this table, a corresponding entry of this table will be added.

agentDaiVlanConfigEntry.name: agentDaiVlanConfigEntry
agentDaiVlanConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration for Dynamic ARP Inspection at each existing VLAN.

agentDaiVlanIndex.name: agentDaiVlanIndex
agentDaiVlanIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN number on which Dynamic ARP Inspection feature is configured.

agentDaiVlanDynArpInspEnable.name: agentDaiVlanDynArpInspEnable
agentDaiVlanDynArpInspEnable.description: This object indicates whether Dynamic ARP Inspection is enabled in this VLAN. If this object is set to 'true', Dynamic ARP Inspection is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', Dynamic ARP Inspection is disabled.

agentDaiVlanLoggingEnable.name: agentDaiVlanLoggingEnable
agentDaiVlanLoggingEnable.description: This object indicates whether the Dynamic ARP Inspection logging is enabled on this VlAN. If this object is set to 'true', Dynamic ARP Inspection logging is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', Dynamic ARP Inspection loging is disabled.

agentDaiVlanArpAclName.name: agentDaiVlanArpAclName
agentDaiVlanArpAclName.description: This object indicates the ARP ACL name set for this VLAN.

agentDaiVlanArpAclStaticFlag.name: agentDaiVlanArpAclStaticFlag
agentDaiVlanArpAclStaticFlag.description: This object indicates whether the ARP ACL set for this VLAN has static flag set. If this object is set to 'true', static flag is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', static flag is disabled.

agentDaiStatsReset.name: agentDaiStatsReset
agentDaiStatsReset.description: Clear the DAI statistics on all vlans. A value of reset(1) is used to reset the statistics. A read on this object will always return the value none(0). The value none(0) cannot be forcibly set by the administrator.

agentDaiVlanStatsTable.name: agentDaiVlanStatsTable
agentDaiVlanStatsTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to control Dynamic ARP Inspection per VLAN. When a VLAN is created in a device supporting this table, a corresponding entry of this table will be added.

agentDaiVlanStatsEntry.name: agentDaiVlanStatsEntry
agentDaiVlanStatsEntry.description: A row instance contains the Dynamic ARP Inspection statistics per VLAN.

agentDaiVlanStatsIndex.name: agentDaiVlanStatsIndex
agentDaiVlanStatsIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN number on which Dynamic ARP Inspection statistics are retrieved.

agentDaiVlanPktsForwarded.name: agentDaiVlanPktsForwarded
agentDaiVlanPktsForwarded.description: Number of valid ARP packets forwarded by DAI.

agentDaiVlanPktsDropped.name: agentDaiVlanPktsDropped
agentDaiVlanPktsDropped.description: Number of invalid ARP packets dropped by DAI.

agentDaiVlanDhcpDrops.name: agentDaiVlanDhcpDrops
agentDaiVlanDhcpDrops.description: Number of ARP packets that were dropped by DAI as there is no matching DHCP Snooping binding entry found.

agentDaiVlanDhcpPermits.name: agentDaiVlanDhcpPermits
agentDaiVlanDhcpPermits.description: Number of ARP packets that were forwarded by DAI as there is a matching DHCP Snooping binding entry found.

agentDaiVlanAclDrops.name: agentDaiVlanAclDrops
agentDaiVlanAclDrops.description: Number of ARP packets that were dropped by DAI as there is no matching ARP ACL rule found for this Vlan and the static flag is set on this vlan.

agentDaiVlanAclPermits.name: agentDaiVlanAclPermits
agentDaiVlanAclPermits.description: Number of ARP packets that were permitted by DAI as there is a matching ARP ACL rule found for this Vlan.

agentDaiVlanSrcMacFailures.name: agentDaiVlanSrcMacFailures
agentDaiVlanSrcMacFailures.description: Number of ARP packets that were dropped by DAI as the sender mac address in ARP packet didn't match the source mac in ethernet header.

agentDaiVlanDstMacFailures.name: agentDaiVlanDstMacFailures
agentDaiVlanDstMacFailures.description: Number of ARP packets that were dropped by DAI as the target mac address in ARP reply packet didn't match the destination mac in ethernet header.

agentDaiVlanIpValidFailures.name: agentDaiVlanIpValidFailures
agentDaiVlanIpValidFailures.description: Number of ARP packets that were dropped by DAI as the sender IP address in ARP packet or target IP address in ARP reply packet is invalid. Invalid addresses include 0.0.0.0, 255.255.255.255, IP multicast addresses, class E addresses (240.0.0.0/4), loopback addresses (127.0.0.0/8).

agentDaiIfConfigTable.name: agentDaiIfConfigTable
agentDaiIfConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to configure the trust state for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose at each physical interface capable of this feature.

agentDaiIfConfigEntry.name: agentDaiIfConfigEntry
agentDaiIfConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration for Dynamic ARP Inspection at each physical interface capable of this feature.

agentDaiIfTrustEnable.name: agentDaiIfTrustEnable
agentDaiIfTrustEnable.description: This object indicates whether the interface is trusted for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose. If this object is set to 'true', the interface is trusted. ARP packets coming to this interface will be forwarded without checking. If this object is set to 'false', the interface is not trusted. ARP packets coming to this interface will be subjected to ARP inspection.

agentDaiIfRateLimit.name: agentDaiIfRateLimit
agentDaiIfRateLimit.description: This object indicates rate limit value for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose. If the incoming rate of ARP packets exceeds the value of this object for consecutively burst interval seconds, ARP packets will be dropped. Value of -1 indicates that there is no rate limit.

agentDaiIfBurstInterval.name: agentDaiIfBurstInterval
agentDaiIfBurstInterval.description: This object indicates the burst interval value for rate limiting purpose on this interface.

agentArpAclTable.name: agentArpAclTable
agentArpAclTable.description: A table of the ARP ACL entries

agentArpAclEntry.name: agentArpAclEntry
agentArpAclEntry.description: Represents entry for an ARP ACL

agentArpAclName.name: agentArpAclName
agentArpAclName.description: Name of the ARP ACL, which must consist of 1 to 31 alphanumeric characters and uniquely identify this ARP ACL. This object must be set to complete a new ARP ACL row instance.

agentArpAclRowStatus.name: agentArpAclRowStatus
agentArpAclRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. Entries can not be deleted until all rows in arpAclRuleTable with corresponding values of arpAclIndex have been deleted. active(1) - this ACL instance is active createAndGo(4) - set to this value to create an instance destroy(6) - set to this value to delete an instance

agentArpAclRuleTable.name: agentArpAclRuleTable
agentArpAclRuleTable.description: A table of the ARP ACL Rule entries

agentArpAclRuleEntry.name: agentArpAclRuleEntry
agentArpAclRuleEntry.description: Represents entry for a set of ARP ACL-match rules

agentArpAclRuleMatchSenderIpAddr.name: agentArpAclRuleMatchSenderIpAddr
agentArpAclRuleMatchSenderIpAddr.description: Sender IP address match value for the ARP ACL.

agentArpAclRuleMatchSenderMacAddr.name: agentArpAclRuleMatchSenderMacAddr
agentArpAclRuleMatchSenderMacAddr.description: Sender MAC address match value for the ARP ACL.

agentArpAclRuleRowStatus.name: agentArpAclRuleRowStatus
agentArpAclRuleRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. active(1) - this ACL Rule is active createAndGo(4) - set to this value to create an instance destroy(6) - set to this value to delete an instance

agentDhcpSnoopingAdminMode.name: agentDhcpSnoopingAdminMode
agentDhcpSnoopingAdminMode.description: This object indicates whether DHCP Snooping is enabled globally. If this object is set to 'true',admin mode is enabled globally. If this object is set to 'false',admin mode is disabled globally.

agentDhcpSnoopingVerifyMac.name: agentDhcpSnoopingVerifyMac
agentDhcpSnoopingVerifyMac.description: This object indicates whether source Mac address in the received DHCP Message needs to be verified or not. If this object is set to 'true',verifyMac is enabled globally. If this object is set to 'false',verifyMac is disabled globally.

agentDhcpSnoopingVlanConfigTable.name: agentDhcpSnoopingVlanConfigTable
agentDhcpSnoopingVlanConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to control DHCP SNOOPING per VLAN. When a VLAN is created in a device supporting this table, a corresponding entry of this table will be added.

agentDhcpSnoopingVlanConfigEntry.name: agentDhcpSnoopingVlanConfigEntry
agentDhcpSnoopingVlanConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration for DHCP SNOOPING at each existing VLAN.

agentDhcpSnoopingVlanIndex.name: agentDhcpSnoopingVlanIndex
agentDhcpSnoopingVlanIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN number on which DHCP SNOOPING Inspection feature is configured.

agentDhcpSnoopingVlanEnable.name: agentDhcpSnoopingVlanEnable
agentDhcpSnoopingVlanEnable.description: This object indicates whether DHCP SNOOPING is enabled in this VLAN. If this object is set to 'true', DHCP SNOOPING is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', DHCP SNOOPING is disabled.

agentDhcpSnoopingIfConfigTable.name: agentDhcpSnoopingIfConfigTable
agentDhcpSnoopingIfConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to configure the trust state for DHCP snooping purpose at each physical interface capable of this feature.

agentDhcpSnoopingIfConfigEntry.name: agentDhcpSnoopingIfConfigEntry
agentDhcpSnoopingIfConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration for DHCP snooping at each physical interface capable of this feature.

agentDhcpSnoopingIfTrustEnable.name: agentDhcpSnoopingIfTrustEnable
agentDhcpSnoopingIfTrustEnable.description: This object indicates whether the interface is trusted for DHCP snooping purpose.

agentDhcpSnoopingIfLogEnable.name: agentDhcpSnoopingIfLogEnable
agentDhcpSnoopingIfLogEnable.description: This object indicates whether the Logging needs on DHCP snooping validations or not

agentDhcpSnoopingIfRateLimit.name: agentDhcpSnoopingIfRateLimit
agentDhcpSnoopingIfRateLimit.description: This object indicates rate limit value for DHCP Snooping purpose. If the incoming rate of DHCP packets exceeds the value of this object for consecutively burst interval seconds, DHCP packets will be dropped. Value of -1 indicates that there is no rate limit.

agentDhcpSnoopingIfBurstInterval.name: agentDhcpSnoopingIfBurstInterval
agentDhcpSnoopingIfBurstInterval.description: This object indicates the burst interval value for rate limiting purpose on this interface. Value of -1 indicates that there is no burst interval.

agentIpsgIfConfigTable.name: agentIpsgIfConfigTable
agentIpsgIfConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to configure the IPSG at each physical interface capable of this feature.

agentIpsgIfConfigEntry.name: agentIpsgIfConfigEntry
agentIpsgIfConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration for IPSG at each physical interface capable of this feature.

agentIpsgIfVerifySource.name: agentIpsgIfVerifySource
agentIpsgIfVerifySource.description: This object indicates whether IP packets received on this interface are filtered based on whether IP Source Guard considers the source IP address to be a valid client address. Setting this variable to false automatically sets agentIpsgIfPortSecurity to false.

agentIpsgIfPortSecurity.name: agentIpsgIfPortSecurity
agentIpsgIfPortSecurity.description: This object indicates whether IP packets received on this interface are filtered based on whether IP Source Guard considers the source MAC address to be a valid client address. The port security option cannot be enabled unless agentIpsgIfVerifySource is also enabled. That is, MAC address filtering cannot be done without also doing IP address filtering. But IP address filtering can be done without MAC address filtering. Once the port security option is enabled, it can only be disabled by disabling agentIpsgIfVerifySource.

agentDhcpSnoopingStatsReset.name: agentDhcpSnoopingStatsReset
agentDhcpSnoopingStatsReset.description: Clear the DHCP snooping statistics on all ports. A value of reset(1) is used to reset the statistics. A read on this object will always return the value none(0). The value none(0) cannot be forcibly set by the administrator.

agentDhcpSnoopingStatsTable.name: agentDhcpSnoopingStatsTable
agentDhcpSnoopingStatsTable.description: A table provides the mechanism for statics of DHCP snooping.

agentDhcpSnoopingStatsEntry.name: agentDhcpSnoopingStatsEntry
agentDhcpSnoopingStatsEntry.description: A row instance contains the DHCP snooping statistics per VLAN.

agentDhcpSnoopingMacVerifyFailures.name: agentDhcpSnoopingMacVerifyFailures
agentDhcpSnoopingMacVerifyFailures.description: This object indicates the number of failure verifications of client mac address with source mac address
